.SH "NAME"
Test2::Manual::Anatomy::Utilities \- Overview of utilities for Test2.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This is a brief overview of the utilities provided by Test2.
.SH "Test2::Util"
.IX Header "Test2::Util"
Test2::Util provides functions to help you find out about the current
system, or to run generic tasks that tend to be Test2 specific.
.PP
This utility provides things like an internal \f(CW\*(C`try {...}\*(C'\fR implementation, and
constants for things like threading and forking support.
.SH "Test2::Util::ExternalMeta"
.IX Header "Test2::Util::ExternalMeta"
Test2::Util::ExternalMeta allows you to quickly and easily attach meta-data
to an object class.
.SH "Test2::Util::Facets2Legacy"
.IX Header "Test2::Util::Facets2Legacy"
Test2::Util::Facets2Legacy is a set of functions you can import into a more
recent event class to provide the classic event \s-1API.\s0
.SH "Test2::Util::HashBase"
.IX Header "Test2::Util::HashBase"
Test2::Util::HashBase is a local copy of Object::HashBase. All object
classes provided by Test2 use this to generate methods and accessors.
